transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, I am calling with a concern.

Speaker 1: I just received a second refill on this prescription in as many weeks.

Speaker 2: I'm confused as to why I've got a duplicate prescription sent to the house.

Speaker 1: I want to make sure I'm not on some automatic refill program because I don't want to be on that.

Speaker 2: Yes, so basically every prescription since it's through Pfizer,

Speaker 1: they have a set refill date that needs to be activated so that way the prescription can start.

Speaker 2: Only that, other than that though, on my end,

Speaker 1: I could always take a look at your prescription and see if I can make any modifications.

Speaker 2: What's your last name?

Speaker 1: Okay, it's Boye, B-O-Y-E, 04676.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I pulled up your profile, sir.

Speaker 1: I do see you're currently one of our VIP members for the Viagra AGV.

Speaker 2: I do want to mention that the script right now has a refill every month,

Speaker 1: so what I could do for you so you don't lose access to your prescription,

Speaker 2: I can go ahead and just modify the refills so that way you don't continue to receive them every month.

Speaker 1: My system lets me freeze everything out for half a year.

Speaker 2: That way you can go ahead and just call us when you need it or call us to delay it.

Speaker 1: You can delay it and put it on pause until I call back for a refill.

Speaker 2: How's that?

Speaker 1: Right, so I'll freeze it out.

Speaker 2: The system lets me do it for half a year.

Speaker 1: You can always call to freeze it further.

Speaker 2: Aside from that though, you're more than welcome to reach out whenever you need it sooner.

Speaker 1: Okay, very good.

Speaker 2: Thanks so much.

Speaker 1: I can call this customer care number to take care of those changes.

Speaker 2: All right, very well.

Speaker 1: All right, you're all set, sir.

Speaker 2: You have a great day.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: Have a good weekend.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: All right, bye.
